# LiquidDoc Documentation Standards

## Overview
LiquidDoc is Shopify's official documentation system for Liquid snippets and blocks that provides structured documentation, real-time validation, and enhanced editor features. All Liquid snippets and blocks must use LiquidDoc notation.

## Required Documentation Structure
Every snippet and block file must include LiquidDoc documentation at the top using the `{% doc %}` tag:

### Basic Template
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Brief description of what the snippet/block does
  
  @param {type} param_name - Description of the parameter
  @param {type} [optional_param] - Optional parameter description
  
  @example
  {% render 'snippet-name', param_name: value, optional_param: value %}
{% enddoc %}
```

## Parameter Documentation Standards

### Required Format
`@param {type} name - description`

### Parameter Types
- **`{string}`** - Text values
- **`{number}`** - Numeric values  
- **`{boolean}`** - True/false values
- **`{object}`** - Complex Liquid types or non-primitive values

### Parameter Naming
- **Required parameters**: Document without brackets
- **Optional parameters**: Wrap in square brackets `[param_name]`
- **Unique names**: Each parameter must have a unique name
- **Descriptive names**: Use clear, meaningful parameter identifiers

### Default Values
- **Do NOT use** `=value` syntax in parameter documentation (e.g., `[isMain=false]`)
- **Document default values** in the parameter description instead
- **Correct format**: `@param {boolean} [isMain] - Whether this is the main product page (default: false)`
- **Incorrect format**: `@param {boolean} [isMain=false] - Whether this is the main product page`

### Examples
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Product card snippet
  
  @param {string} title - Main product title
  @param {number} price - Product price value
  @param {boolean} show_vendor - Whether to display vendor name
  @param {object} product - Product object
  @param {string} [subtitle] - Optional secondary text
  @param {boolean} [isMain] - Whether this is the main product page (default: false)
  @param {number} [quantity] - Product quantity (default: 1)
{% enddoc %}
```

## Description Standards

### Primary Description
- Place the main description before any `@` annotations
- Explain the purpose and functionality clearly
- Keep it concise but informative

### @description Tag
- Use `@description` tag for additional descriptions
- Only the first description appears in hover tooltips
- Multi-line descriptions are automatically formatted

## Example Documentation

### Multiple Examples
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Price display snippet
  
  @param {number} price - Price value
  @param {boolean} [show_compare_at] - Whether to show compare-at price
  
  @example
  {% render 'price', price: product.price, show_compare_at: true %}
  
  @example
  {% render 'price',
    price: variant.price,
    show_compare_at: false
  %}
{% enddoc %}
```

## Editor Integration Benefits
LiquidDoc provides real-time development assistance:

### Hover Documentation
- Comprehensive parameter information on hover
- Type validation and suggestions
- Usage examples display

### Code Completion
- Smart parameter suggestions
- Automatic parameter name completion
- Type-aware recommendations

### Parameter Validation
- Warnings for missing required parameters
- Type mismatch detection
- Unrecognized parameter warnings

### Theme Check Integration
LiquidDoc works with Shopify's Theme Check tool for validation:

#### Documentation Checks
- **UniqueDocParamNames**: Ensures unique parameter names
- **UnsupportedDocTag**: Validates `doc` tag usage in snippets only
- **ValidDocParamTypes**: Validates parameter type definitions
- **UnusedDocParam**: Ensures documented parameters are used

#### Usage Checks
- **MissingRenderSnippetArguments**: Validates required parameters
- **UnrecognizedRenderSnippetArguments**: Catches unknown parameters
- **ValidRenderSnippetArgumentTypes**: Type validation
- **DuplicateRenderSnippetArguments**: Prevents duplicate parameters

## Implementation Rules

### File Requirements
- **Snippets**: Must include LiquidDoc documentation
- **Blocks**: Must include LiquidDoc documentation
- **Sections**: Schema documentation is separate from LiquidDoc
- **Layouts/Templates**: No LiquidDoc required

### Documentation Quality Standards
1. **Completeness**: Document all parameters with types and descriptions
2. **Accuracy**: Ensure documentation matches actual implementation
3. **Examples**: Provide practical usage examples
4. **Clarity**: Use clear, concise language
5. **Consistency**: Follow established patterns throughout the codebase

### Validation Requirements
- All new snippets/blocks must pass Theme Check validation
- Existing code should be updated to meet LiquidDoc standards
- Parameter types must match actual usage
- All documented parameters must be used in the code

## Best Practices

### Parameter Documentation
- Start with required parameters
- Group related parameters together
- Use consistent formatting and spacing
- Provide meaningful default value examples

### Example Documentation
- Show common use cases
- Include edge case examples
- Demonstrate parameter combinations
- Use realistic, practical examples

### Maintenance
- Keep documentation current with code changes
- Review and update during code reviews
- Validate documentation with Theme Check
- Remove documentation for unused parameters

## Common Patterns

### Product-Related Snippets
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Product display component
  
  @param {object} product - Product object to display
  @param {boolean} [show_price] - Whether to display price
  @param {boolean} [show_vendor] - Whether to display vendor
  @param {string} [image_size] - Image size variant
{% enddoc %}
```

### Navigation Snippets
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Navigation menu component
  
  @param {array} menu_items - Array of menu items
  @param {string} [menu_class] - CSS class for styling
  @param {boolean} [show_icons] - Whether to display icons
{% enddoc %}
```

### Form Snippets
```liquid
{% doc %}
  Form input component
  
  @param {string} field_name - Form field name
  @param {string} [placeholder] - Placeholder text
  @param {string} [field_type] - Input type (text, email, etc.)
  @param {boolean} [required] - Whether field is required
{% enddoc %}
```

## Enforcement
- **Mandatory**: All new snippets and blocks must use LiquidDoc
- **Code Reviews**: Documentation quality must be reviewed
- **Theme Check**: All documentation must pass validation
- **Maintenance**: Existing code should be updated to standards
- **Training**: Team members must understand LiquidDoc syntax